---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../styles/hero.css';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy — SlopTotal" description="How SlopTotal handles your data. No tracking, no third-party sharing, local analysis." canonical="https://sloptotal.com/privacy">
    <section class="legal-page">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: February 2026</p>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <p>
            When you submit text or a URL for analysis, we process it on our servers using local AI
            detection engines. We do <strong>not</strong> send your submitted content to any third-party
            services — all 23 engines run locally on our infrastructure.
        </p>

        <h2>Data retention</h2>
        <p>
            Analysis reports are stored temporarily so they can be viewed and shared via their unique
            report URL. Reports are automatically deleted after <strong>30 days</strong>. We do not
            keep copies of the original submitted text beyond what is shown in the report excerpt.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies &amp; tracking</h2>
        <p>
            SlopTotal does not use cookies, analytics trackers, or fingerprinting. We do not run
            Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, or any equivalent. The site uses no third-party
            JavaScript except Google Fonts for typography.
        </p>

        <h2>Chrome extension</h2>
        <p>
            The SlopTotal Chrome extension communicates only with the API server you configure
            (defaults to your own local instance). It does not transmit data to any other endpoint.
            The extension stores your preferences (toggle states, API URL) in local browser storage
            only.
        </p>

        <h2>Rate limiting</h2>
        <p>
            We apply rate limiting to prevent abuse. Your IP address may be processed
            for this purpose. The website is hosted on GitHub Pages.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
            For privacy questions, open an issue on the project's GitHub repository or email the
            maintainer at the address listed there.
        </p>
    </section>
</Base>
